## 2. Color Palette

### Design Direction: Warm Light Theme with Depth

Avoid the cold sterility of pure whites and bright blues. Instead, use a warm-neutral base with a distinctive teal-slate accent -- architectural and calm, not generic SaaS blue.

### New Palette for `variables.css`

```css
:root {
  /* Blueprint/Canvas colors */
  --color-background: #FAFAF8;          /* Warm off-white canvas - subtle warmth */
  --color-wall-fill: #2C3340;           /* Slightly warmer dark */
  --color-wall-stroke: #1B1F27;         /* Near-black, warm undertone */
  --color-grid-minor: #E8E8E4;          /* Warm grid lines */
  --color-grid-major: #D4D4CE;          /* Warm major grid */
  --color-selection: #0D7C66;           /* Teal - distinctive, architectural */
  --color-selection-fill: rgba(13, 124, 102, 0.07);

  /* UI colors */
  --color-text-primary: #1A1D23;        /* Near-black, warm */
  --color-text-secondary: #6B7080;      /* Muted warm gray */
  --color-text-tertiary: #9CA0AB;       /* For hints, placeholders */
  --color-panel-bg: #F3F3F0;            /* Warm panel background */
  --color-panel-bg-alt: #FAFAF8;        /* Alternate/input background */
  --color-surface-elevated: #FFFFFF;    /* For inputs, cards - true white for contrast */
  --color-border: #DDDDD8;             /* Warm border */
  --color-border-subtle: #EAEAE6;       /* Lighter border for inner separators */
  --color-accent: #0D7C66;             /* Teal accent */
  --color-accent-hover: #0A6654;        /* Darker teal on hover */
  --color-accent-subtle: rgba(13, 124, 102, 0.08);  /* Teal tint for selected states */
  --color-danger: #C4342D;              /* Warmer red */
  --color-danger-hover: #A52B25;        /* Darker danger */
  --color-danger-subtle: #FFF5F4;       /* Danger background tint */

  /* Shadows - layered depth system */
  --shadow-sm: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
  --shadow-md: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06), 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
  --shadow-lg: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08), 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
  --shadow-overlay: 0 16px 48px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12), 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);

  /* Layout */
  --toolbar-height: 48px;
  --sidebar-width: 244px;               /* Slightly wider for breathing room */
  --properties-width: 284px;            /* Slightly wider */

  /* Typography */
  --font-ui: 'DM Sans', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
  --font-blueprint: 'JetBrains Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;

  /* Spacing */
  --space-xs: 4px;
  --space-sm: 8px;
  --space-md: 12px;
  --space-lg: 16px;
  --space-xl: 24px;

  /* Borders */
  --radius-sm: 5px;                     /* Slightly rounder than 4px */
  --radius-md: 8px;                     /* More visible rounding */
  --radius-lg: 12px;                    /* For modals, large cards */

  /* Transitions */
  --ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
  --duration-fast: 0.12s;
  --duration-normal: 0.2s;
}
```

### Rationale

- **Teal accent (`#0D7C66`)**: Distinctive, avoids generic blue. Evokes architectural materials (verdigris, patina). High contrast on light backgrounds. Works beautifully for selection highlights and active states.
- **Warm neutrals**: The `#F3F3F0` panel background and `#FAFAF8` canvas background have a subtle warm undertone that prevents the interface from feeling clinical. Architectural software should feel like a workshop, not a hospital.
- **Shadow system**: Three tiers of shadows create spatial hierarchy without borders everywhere.

