              transform var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-out);
}

.deleteBtn:hover {
  background: var(--color-danger-hover);
}

.deleteBtn:active {
  transform: scale(0.97);
}

.summary {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.7;
}

.unitToggle {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-sm);
  margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
}

.unitToggle span {
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
}

.unitBtn {
  height: 24px;
  padding: 0 10px;
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 600;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  background: var(--color-surface-elevated);
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: all var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-out);
}

.unitBtn:hover {
  border-color: #C0C0BA;
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
}

.unitBtnActive {
  background: var(--color-accent);
  color: white;
  border-color: var(--color-accent);
}

.unitBtnActive:hover {
  background: var(--color-accent-hover);
  border-color: var(--color-accent-hover);
}
```

### Key Changes
- **Subtitle sections get a subtle top border**: Creates visual separation between property groups without heavy visual weight
- **Color hex values use monospace font**: Appropriate for technical values
- **Negative letter-spacing on title**: Tighter tracking on larger text feels more authoritative
- **Consistent 30px button height**: Matches toolbar
- **Scale micro-interaction on delete button**: Consistent press feel

---

## 7. SVG Canvas and Status Bar (`SvgCanvas.module.css`)

### Full Updated Styles

```css
.canvasContainer {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  overflow: hidden;
  position: relative;
  background: var(--color-background);
}

.svg {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  display: block;
}

.statusBar {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  height: 26px;
  background: var(--color-panel-bg);
  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-xl);
  padding: 0 var(--space-lg);
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  font-family: var(--font-blueprint);
  letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  /* Subtle inner shadow at top */
  box-shadow: inset 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02);
  user-select: none;
}

.statusMessage {
  margin-left: auto;
  color: var(--color-accent);
  font-family: var(--font-ui);
  font-weight: 500;
  /* Fade-in animation */
  animation: fadeIn var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out);
}

@keyframes fadeIn {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(2px); }
  to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}
```

### Key Changes
- **Height increased to 26px**: Slightly more breathing room for the monospace text
- **Gap increased to 24px**: Wider separation between status items for easier scanning
- **Padding to 16px**: Aligns with sidebar/properties panel padding
- **`user-select: none`**: Status bar text should not be selectable
- **Status message animation**: Subtle fade-in-up when messages appear, making them noticeable without being jarring
- **Status message uses UI font**: Differentiates informational messages from coordinate readouts

---

## 8. Modal Styling (`Modal.jsx`)

The Modal uses inline styles, so the changes go directly into the JSX. Here are the exact new inline style objects:

### Overlay Style

```js
{
  position: 'fixed',
  inset: 0,
  background: 'rgba(10, 12, 15, 0.45)',
  backdropFilter: 'blur(4px)',
  WebkitBackdropFilter: 'blur(4px)',
  display: 'flex',
  alignItems: 'center',
  justifyContent: 'center',
  zIndex: 1000,
  animation: 'modalOverlayIn 0.2s ease-out',
}
```

### Dialog Style

```js
{
  background: '#FAFAF8',
  borderRadius: 'var(--radius-lg)',
  padding: '28px',
  minWidth: '380px',
  maxWidth: '480px',
  boxShadow: 'var(--shadow-overlay)',
  border: '1px solid var(--color-border)',
  animation: 'modalDialogIn 0.25s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)',
}
```

### Title Style

```js
{
  margin: '0 0 20px',
  fontSize: '16px',
  fontWeight: 600,
  letterSpacing: '-0.01em',
  color: 'var(--color-text-primary)',
}
```

### CSS Keyframes to Add to `global.css`

```css
@keyframes modalOverlayIn {
  from { opacity: 0; }
  to { opacity: 1; }
}

@keyframes modalDialogIn {
  from { opacity: 0; transform: scale(0.96) translateY(8px); }
  to { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1) translateY(0); }
}
```

### Key Changes
- **Backdrop blur**: `4px` blur on the overlay creates depth without fully obscuring context -- user can still sense what is behind the modal
- **Darker overlay**: `rgba(10, 12, 15, 0.45)` instead of `rgba(0,0,0,0.4)` -- slightly warmer black
- **Entry animation**: Modal scales up from 96% and slides up 8px, creating a natural "rising into view" feel
- **Warm background**: `#FAFAF8` instead of pure white, consistent with the palette
- **Larger radius**: `--radius-lg` (12px) for the modal -- larger surfaces get larger radii
- **Border**: 1px border prevents the shadow from feeling "floaty" on light backgrounds

---

## 9. InputField Inline Style Updates (`InputField.jsx`)

Since InputField uses inline styles, here are the exact updated style objects:

### Container `<div>` style

```js
{
  display: 'flex',
  alignItems: 'center',
  gap: '8px',
  marginBottom: '6px',   /* Tighter than 8px for denser property list */
}
```

### Label style

```js
{
  flex: '0 0 80px',
  fontSize: '12px',
  color: 'var(--color-text-secondary)',
}
```

### Input style

```js
{
  flex: 1,
  minWidth: 0,
  height: '28px',
  padding: '0 8px',
  border: '1px solid var(--color-border)',
  borderRadius: 'var(--radius-sm)',
  fontSize: '12px',
  fontFamily: type === 'number' ? 'var(--font-blueprint)' : 'inherit',
  background: readOnly ? 'var(--color-panel-bg)' : 'var(--color-surface-elevated)',
  color: readOnly ? 'var(--color-text-secondary)' : 'var(--color-text-primary)',
  transition: 'border-color 0.12s, box-shadow 0.12s',
}
```

### Suffix style

```js
{
  fontSize: '10px',
  color: 'var(--color-text-tertiary)',
  fontFamily: 'var(--font-blueprint)',
  minWidth: '22px',
}
```

### Key Changes
- **Numeric inputs use monospace font**: Technical values (coordinates, measurements) should be in `JetBrains Mono` for precision alignment
- **Suffix uses monospace**: Unit labels (mm, m, deg) also monospace, smaller (10px), and in tertiary color
- **Tighter row spacing**: 6px margin-bottom instead of 8px -- properties panels can be dense
- **Surface-elevated for editable inputs**: True white background distinguishes editable from read-only
- **Transition added**: Border and shadow animate smoothly on focus

Note: The focus state styling requires either CSS (preferred) or an `onFocus`/`onBlur` handler. Since this component uses inline styles, the simplest approach is to add a CSS class in `global.css`:

```css
/* In global.css */
input:not([readonly]):hover {
  border-color: #C0C0BA;
}

input:not([readonly]):focus {
  border-color: var(--color-accent);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(13, 124, 102, 0.08);
  outline: none;
}

select:hover {
  border-color: #C0C0BA;
}

select:focus {
  border-color: var(--color-accent);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(13, 124, 102, 0.08);
  outline: none;
}
```

---

## 10. App Layout (`App.module.css`)

### Full Updated Styles

```css
.layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-rows: var(--toolbar-height) 1fr;
  grid-template-columns:
    var(--layout-sidebar-width, var(--sidebar-width))
    1fr
    var(--layout-properties-width, var(--properties-width));
  grid-template-areas:
    "toolbar toolbar toolbar"
    "sidebar canvas properties";
  height: 100%;
  width: 100%;
}

.toolbar {
  grid-area: toolbar;
  z-index: 10;
}

.sidebar {
  grid-area: sidebar;
  min-height: 0;
  overflow-y: auto;
  transition: width var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out);
}

.canvas {
  grid-area: canvas;
  min-width: 0;
  /* Subtle inset shadow to create depth - canvas feels recessed */
  box-shadow: inset 1px 0 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03),
              inset -1px 0 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03),
              inset 0 1px 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
}

.properties {
  grid-area: properties;
}

.panelHidden {
  display: none;
}
```

### Key Changes
- **Canvas inset shadow**: Very subtle inset shadows on the canvas area make it feel physically recessed between the sidebar and properties panel, creating a natural depth hierarchy
- **Toolbar z-index**: Ensures toolbar shadow renders above canvas
- **Sidebar transition**: Smooth width transition when collapsing/expanding (though `display: none` on `.panelHidden` currently prevents this from animating -- this is noted as a future consideration)

---

